<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="67" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName LSID="F83A8A95-C026-F3B0-EF95-D98C7C67B35E" authority="Morimoto, 1962: 47" authorityName="Morimoto" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Othippiini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Othippiini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Othippiini Morimoto, 1962: 47</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="67" type="classificatory history and current circumscription">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="67">Classificatory history and current circumscription.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="67">
Eleven genera were first grouped into tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Morimoto, 1962" authorityName="Morimoto" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Othippiini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Othippiini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Othippiini</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hustache, A" journalOrPublisher="Sborni ́ k Entomologicke ́ ho oddele ̌ ni ́ pr ̌ i zoologicky ́ ch sbi ́ rka ́ ch Na ́ rodni ́ ho musea v Praze" pageId="56" pageNumber="107" pagination="58 - 82" refId="B86" refString="Hustache, A, 1938. Zygopinae de L'Amerique meridionale. Sborník Entomologického oddelění při zoologických sbírkách Národního musea v Praze 16: 58 - 82" title="Zygopinae de L'Amerique meridionale." volume="16" year="1938">Hustache (1938</bibRefCitation>
: 63), which was not treated as a valid name in the catalog of 
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, MA" journalOrPublisher="Entomopraxis, Barcelona" pageId="51" pageNumber="102" refId="B1" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, MA, Lyal, CHC, 1999. A world catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae). Entomopraxis, Barcelona" title="A world catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae)." year="1999">Alonso-Zarazaga and Lyal (1999</bibRefCitation>
: 113) for lacking a description. Morimoto (1962: 47) provided some clarification on the distinction of the tribe, and this was further refined in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kojima, H" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B97" refString="Kojima, H, Lyal, CHC, 2002. New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Esakia 42: 161 - 174" title="New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="42" year="2002">Kojima and Lyal (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, where seven genera were transferred out of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Morimoto, 1962" authorityName="Morimoto" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Othippiini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Othippiini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Othippiini</taxonomicName>
in order to redefine it. Othippiines can be distinguished (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="67">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kojima, H" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B97" refString="Kojima, H, Lyal, CHC, 2002. New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Esakia 42: 161 - 174" title="New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="42" year="2002">Kojima and Lyal 2002</bibRefCitation>
: 172) by the following combination of characters: the mesepisterna are non-ascending, the scutellum is exposed, the prosternum of most is canaliculate, and the antennal funiculus has 7 articles. However, the monophyly of the tribe has yet to be shown (
<bibRefCitation author="Kojima, H" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B97" refString="Kojima, H, Lyal, CHC, 2002. New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Esakia 42: 161 - 174" title="New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="42" year="2002">Kojima and Lyal 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="67" type="variation">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="67">Variation in key character systems.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="67">
The mesoventrite of othippiines can have a rostral channel or be unmodified (
<bibRefCitation author="Kojima, H" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B97" refString="Kojima, H, Lyal, CHC, 2002. New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Esakia 42: 161 - 174" title="New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="42" year="2002">Kojima and Lyal 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The number of antennal funicular articles for othippiines given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kojima, H" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B97" refString="Kojima, H, Lyal, CHC, 2002. New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Esakia 42: 161 - 174" title="New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="42" year="2002">Kojima and Lyal (2002)</bibRefCitation>
serves to separate this tribe from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1865" lsidName="" pageId="16" pageNumber="67" rank="tribe" tribe="Mecopini">Mecopini</taxonomicName>
which have been considered to have 6 articles since originally described. However, one of the genera currently treated in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1865" lsidName="" pageId="16" pageNumber="67" rank="tribe" tribe="Mecopini">Mecopini</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Emexaure" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Emexaure" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="67">Emexaure</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pascoe, 1871) has a funiculus with 7 articles (
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, FP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Linnean Society of London, Zoology" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" refId="B128" refString="Pascoe, FP, 1871. Catalog of Zygopinae, a subfamily of Curculionidae, found by Mr. Wallace in the Eastern Archipelago. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (4)7(39): 198-222, (40): 256-266." title="Catalog of Zygopinae, a subfamily of Curculionidae, found by Mr. Wallace in the Eastern Archipelago. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (4) 7 (39): 198 - 222, (40): 256 - 266." year="1871">Pascoe 1871</bibRefCitation>
: 216), some of the genera are similar in appearance and also in eye shape (
<bibRefCitation author="Kojima, H" journalOrPublisher="Esakia" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="161 - 174" refId="B97" refString="Kojima, H, Lyal, CHC, 2002. New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Esakia 42: 161 - 174" title="New Oriental and Australian Conoderinae, with taxonomic notes on the tribe Othippiini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="42" year="2002">Kojima and Lyal 2002</bibRefCitation>
: 171) and distinction between the tribes requires further study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="68">
<pageBreakToken pageId="17" pageNumber="68" start="start">Diversity</pageBreakToken>
and distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName authority="Morimoto, 1962" authorityName="Morimoto" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Othippiini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Othippiini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Othippiini</taxonomicName>
now contains eight genera, six of which are currently monotypic. The monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Acoptus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acoptus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="68">Acoptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sole New World representative.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
